                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="antoninewall_sng_1" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a wall built in 142 AD across southern Scotland during the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/reign_1#reign_sng_1" title="reign definition"><span class="ndv">reign</span></a> of the Roman <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/emperor#emperor_topg_1" title="emperor definition"><span class="ndv">emperor</span></a> Antoninus Pius. It was about 37 miles/59 kilometres long and was intended to replace <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/hadrian-s-wall" title="Hadrian's Wall definition"><span class="ndv">Hadrian's Wall</span></a> further south as the northern <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/frontier#frontier_topg_1" title="frontier definition"><span class="ndv">frontier</span></a> of the Roman Empire, but it had to be abandoned by 197 AD. Little of the wall now remains.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
